author: Inside Edition
description: Some families across the country were shocked this past Thanksgiving when they opened a can of Ocean Spray cranberry sauce to find just water in it. Inside Edition spoke with Sandra Kelly, who hosted 15 guests for Thanksgiving at her home in Michigan. She says cranberry sauce is important to her meal and not having it was disappointing. Ocean Spray says, "We're looking into how this may have happened. We've reached out to the folks who shared these videos to learn more and make it right."
title: Ocean Spray Responds To Videos Of Cranberry Cans Filled With Water

author: Inside Edition
description: Dave Coulier, who played Uncle Joey on the classic sitcom "Full House," revealed Tuesday that he is battling a new form of cancer. He broke the news on the "TODAY" show that he has tongue cancer. Last April, Coulier was declared cured of cancer after a battle with non-Hodgkin-lymphoma. The 66-year-old says he is currently undergoing radiation. Coulier says he expects to beat this cancer, just as he did before.
title: 'Full House' Star Dave Coulier Reveals He Has Tongue Cancer

author: Inside Edition
description: Videos show people fleeing the scene of the Black Friday shooting at a mall in San Jose, California, as hundreds ran for their lives. Some people found themselves seeking shelter at a home near the mall, where more than 40 strangers were welcomed. The homeowner stood at the front door to usher in the stream of terror-stricken shoppers. Good Samaritans Martin and Irene Garcia spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall.
title: Homeowners Shelter At Least 40 People Fleeing Black Friday Shooting

author: Inside Edition
description: Micah Smith took his three children on a hike in Utah. The weather turned and a storm blew in. Smith allegedly told his children to tough it out and "march on." The children were rescued the next day after being reported missing by their mom, who was back home. Smith appeared at a hearing Tuesday on child torture and aggravated child abuse charges. Smith's mother-in-law says he tried his best to take care of his kids, adding he had hyperthermia and dehydration and got lost because of the storm.
title: Dad Faces Child Abuse And Torture Charges After Family Hike

author: Inside Edition
description: Sabrina Carpenter spoke out after the White House used one of her songs in a video of ICE agents in action. "The video is evil and disgusting," the singer posted on social media. "Do not ever involve me or my music to benefit your inhumane agenda." Meanwhile, President Donald Trump's late nights may be catching up to him. He seemed to be struggling to stay awake during his cabinet meeting Tuesday.
title: Sabrina Carpenter Condemns White House For Using Her Song

author: Inside Edition
description: A giant bear found a tiny crawl space and made it its home, removing the barricade covering the hole. But, when it came to getting out, the 500-pound bear was stuck. California homeowner Ken Johnson says his unwanted tenant moved in a week ago. Inside Edition's Jim Moret looked into the underground den. In a new development, another bear showed up to check out the joint. Johnson says he called fish and wildlife for advice and they told him to make noise to try to get rid of the bear himself.
title: Man Finds Bear Living Under His Home

author: Inside Edition
description: A South American motorcycle influencer has reportedly died. News outlets in Colombia say Sofia Quiroz was killed in a traffic accident while riding her bike to Floridablanca. They report she was trying to maneuver between a car and a tractor trailer on a highway. They say she fell off the bike and was struck by the tractor trailer. Quiroz was 25. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 'Bikergirl' Sofia Quiroz Dies In Traffic Accident At 25 In Colombia

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say 18-year-old Sawyer Updike was tortured as his frat brothers extinguished cigarettes on his chest and speared his leg with fish hooks. Updike's parents say continuous abuse drove their son to suicide.
title: Parents Say College Student Died By Suicide After Hazing #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt revealed the MRI was focused on the president's heart and abdomen.
title: Why Did Trump Get An MRI? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Accused assassin Luigi Mangione appeared in court Monday as a crucial pre-trial hearing went underway. Prosecutors played the surveillance video showing the shooting of United Health Care CEO Brian Thompson outside the Hilton Hotel in Manhattan.
title: Luigi Mangione Appears In Court #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Thanksgiving almost turned tragic for an elderly driver who police say ran right through a coffee shop. It happened in Los Gatos, California. Police say it was a 90-year-old man behind the wheel of this car that went right into the Los Gatos Coffee Roasting Company. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 90-Year-Old Man Crashes Car Into Coffee Shop On Thanksgiving Night: Cops
